# Blockhouse Authentication App

## Project Overview
A React Native authentication app with login, signup, and home screens, featuring Redux state management and CI/CD pipeline.

## Prerequisites
- Node.js (v18+)
- React Native CLI
- Xcode (for iOS development)
- Android Studio (for Android development)

## Setup Instructions

### 1. Clone the Repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/BlockhouseAuth.git
cd BlockhouseAuth
```

### 2. Install Dependencies
```bash
npm install
```

### 3. iOS Setup (macOS only)
```bash
cd ios
pod install
cd ..
```

### 4. Run the Application

#### For iOS
```bash
npx react-native run-ios
```

#### For Android
```bash
npx react-native run-android
```

## Project Structure
- `src/`
  - `screens/`: Authentication and home screens
  - `navigation/`: App navigation setup
  - `redux/`: State management slices and store
- `.github/workflows/`: CI/CD GitHub Actions configuration

## Available Scripts
- `npm run lint`: Run ESLint
- `npm test`: Run Jest tests
- `npm start`: Start Metro bundler
- `npm run android`: Run app on Android
- `npm run ios`: Run app on iOS

## CI/CD Pipeline
The GitHub Actions workflow handles:
- Linting checks
- Running tests
- Building Android APK
- Building iOS IPA
- Artifact uploads

